simulationMaster.simulation_description: Testing if we are able to create  new simulation

•	Objective of the Scenario: Evaluate L4 d/c ratio with an increase of demand under for SAU 3950900083 GLUCOPHAGE 500MG TABS AG ML - (60) SAU- 80K production in March/April to have ETA in May. Then 120 K production in May to have it ETA June/July

•	Initial configuration: SAU demand with scenario F0 and the current shift model- L4 with 2 shift model in Janury and February and from March 24x6

•	Customized variables: Increase demand  80K production in March/April and 120 K production in May. 24x6 with the D/C ration of L4 is not needed. We are going to reduce the shift model from 24x6 to 24x5 from march to July due to the d/c ratio. As the tool don'ta llow to change the shift model we have changed the OEE 

•	Key performance indicators: D/C ratio of L4 

•	Reason for changes: Evaluate shift model and d/C ratio with the increase of demand

•	Traceability

•	Results and Conclusion: With the reduction of the shift model to 24x5 from April to July and with the additional demanda the d/C ratio is below 70% which means that can absorve the volume of July or the shift model could be adapted
